  "prompt": "What is the best comedy movie ever?",
  "response": "Determining the \"best\" comedy movie ever is highly subjective and depends on personal taste. However, several comedy films are consistently praised by audiences and critics alike. Some of these include:\n\n1. **\"Monty Python and the Holy Grail\" (1975)** - Known for its absurd humor and clever satire.\n2. **\"Airplane!\" (1980)** - Famous for its slapstick comedy and memorable one-liners.\n3. **\"Groundhog Day\" (1993)** - Celebrated for its original concept and Bill Murray's performance.\n4. **\"Some Like It Hot\" (1959)** - A classic, featuring Marilyn Monroe and known for its wit and charm.\n5. **\"The Big Lebowski\" (1998)** - A cult classic with a unique blend of humor and eccentric characters.\n\nUltimately, the best comedy for you will align with your sense of humor and what you find most entertaining.",
